    "Page 18 TheJews On WK people will OMr owe wy A Scripps Howard Newspaper By Carrier Week 10c By Mall Month 60c Year 7 20 1013 13U1 St N W Phone District 7777 LOWELL MEI LETT NELSON P POYNTER Editor Business Manager CAN THE STATES AGREE MERE laymen we have had a hard time trying to under stand why these United States cannot act as a nation to solve a common problem arising from wagecutting competi tion But the Supreme Court said or at least implied that this could not be done under the Constitution We know from a long and sad experience that individual states are powerless to protect labor standards within their own borders so long as the goods they produce must be sold in the same market with cheaplabor goods produced in other states But eminent constitutional lawyers say that the same end can be accomplished thru mutually advantageous compacts between the states They say that representatives of govern ors can sit around a conference table and agree on minimum wages maximum hours and satisfactory working conditions in individual industries They say that such an agreement will become legally binding when ratified by the legislatures of the"
